  "created": "2025-10-13",
  "description": "Bacterial ribosome assembly is a hierarchical, co-transcriptional process involving the coordinated folding of ribosomal RNA (rRNA) and binding of ribosomal proteins (r-proteins). The 30S small subunit and 50S large subunit assemble independently through distinct assembly maps before joining to form the functional 70S ribosome. Assembly is guided by RNA-protein and protein-protein interactions, with specific assembly factors (GTPases, chaperones, methylases) facilitating maturation. The process demonstrates sophisticated quality control mechanisms ensuring only correctly assembled ribosomes enter translation.",
