  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Transcription and RNA Production\n    A[rrn Operon Transcription] --> B[Primary rRNA Transcript]\n    B --> C[RNase III Cleavage]\n    C --> D[16S rRNA Precursor]\n    C --> E[23S rRNA Precursor]\n    C --> F[5S rRNA Precursor]\n    \n    %% 30S Assembly Pathway\n    D --> G[16S rRNA Folding]\n    G --> H[5' Domain Formation]\n    H --> I{Early Proteins<br/>Available?}\n    \n    I -->|Yes| J[Primary Binding Proteins]\n    J --> K[S4 S8 S15 S17 S20 Binding]\n    K --> L[Central Domain Stabilization]\n    L --> M{Secondary Proteins<br/>Ready?}\n    \n    M -->|Yes| N[Secondary Binding Proteins]\n    N --> O[S2 S3 S5 S7 S9 S10 S14 S19 Binding]\n    O --> P[3' Domain Formation]\n    P --> Q{Tertiary Proteins<br/>Ready?}\n    \n    Q -->|Yes| R[Tertiary Binding Proteins]\n    R --> S[S6 S11 S12 S13 S18 S21 Binding]\n    S --> T[Pre-30S Particle]\n    \n    %% 30S Maturation\n    T --> U[RimM Chaperone Action]\n    U --> V[16S 3' End Processing]\n    V --> W[KsgA Methylation]\n    W --> X[Era GTPase Quality Check]\n    X --> ANDGATE1{Correctly Folded AND<br/>Modified?}\n    \n    ANDGATE1 -->|Yes| Y[Mature 30S Subunit]\n    ANDGATE1 -->|No| Z[/Degradation or Repair/]\n    \n    %% 50S Assembly Pathway\n    E --> AA[23S rRNA Folding]\n    F --> AB[5S rRNA Folding]\n    \n    AA --> AC[Domain I Formation]\n    AC --> AD{Early 50S Proteins<br/>Available?}\n    \n    AD -->|Yes| AE[L4 L13 L20 L22 Binding]\n    AE --> AF[Central Protuberance Assembly]\n    AF --> AG[L1 L2 L3 L6 L10 L11 Binding]\n    \n    AB --> AH[5S-L5-L18 Complex]\n    AH --> AI[5S Integration]\n    AI --> AF\n    \n    AG --> AJ{Late 50S Proteins<br/>Ready?}\n    AJ -->|Yes| AK[Remaining Protein Binding]\n    AK --> AL[L7/L12 Stalk Formation]\n    AL --> AM[Pre-50S Particle]\n    \n    %% 50S Maturation\n    AM --> AN[23S rRNA Modifications]\n    AN --> AO[RlmE Methylation]\n    AO --> AP[RluD Pseudouridylation]\n    AP --> AQ[ObgE GTPase Action]\n    AQ --> ANDGATE2{Correctly Assembled AND<br/>Peptidyl Transferase Active?}\n    \n    ANDGATE2 -->|Yes| AR[Mature 50S Subunit]\n    ANDGATE2 -->|No| AS[/Degradation/]\n    \n    %% 70S Formation\n    Y --> AT[30S in Cytoplasm]\n    AR --> AU[50S in Cytoplasm]\n    \n    AT --> AV{Subunits<br/>Available?}\n    AU --> AV\n    \n    AV -->|Yes| AW[30S-50S Association]\n    AW --> AX[70S Ribosome Formation]\n    AX --> AY[Functional Translation Complex]\n    \n    %% Quality Control\n    AY --> AZ[Translation Competence Test]\n    AZ --> BA{Functional?}\n    BA -->|Yes| BB[Active Ribosome Pool]\n    BA -->|No| BC[Ribosome Recycling]\n    \n    %% Styling - GLMP Color Scheme\n    %% Red: Triggers & Inputs\n    \n    %% Yellow: Structures & Objects (Proteins, Factors)\n    \n    %% Green: Processing & Operations\n    \n    %% Blue: Intermediates & States\n    \n    %% Orange: OR Logic Gates\n    \n    %% Lavender: AND Logic Gates\n    \n    %% Violet: Products & Outputs\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style J fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style K fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style L fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style M fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style N fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style O fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style P fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Q fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style R fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style S fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style T fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style U fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style V fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style W fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style X fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style ANDGATE1 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style Y fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Z fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AA fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AD fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AF fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AG fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AH fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AJ fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AK fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AN fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AO fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AP fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AQ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style ANDGATE2 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AR fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AS fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AT fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AU fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AV fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AW fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AX fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AY fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AZ fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BA fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style BB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000",
  "name": "Ribosome Assembly and Maturation",
  "notGates": 2,
  "notes": "This flowchart represents the hierarchical assembly of E. coli ribosomes with 52 nodes showing both 30S and 50S assembly pathways. Contains 7 OR logic gates representing assembly checkpoints (protein availability checks, functional tests) and 2 AND logic gates representing multi-component requirements (30S maturation requires correct folding AND modification; 50S maturation requires correct assembly AND peptidyl transferase activity). The model includes co-transcriptional rRNA processing, hierarchical protein binding (primary, secondary, tertiary), assembly factor-mediated maturation, quality control checkpoints, and final 70S formation. Assembly follows the classic Nomura map but incorporates modern understanding of GTPase checkpoints (Era, ObgE) and modification enzymes (KsgA, RlmE, RluD). The process demonstrates that ribosome assembly is not random aggregation but a programmed, quality-controlled biosynthetic pathway.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "ecoli_transcription_regulation",
    "ecoli_translation_protein_synthesis"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on decades of biochemical reconstitution experiments, cryo-EM structures, and genetic studies of E. coli ribosome biogenesis. The assembly pathway represents the Nomura assembly map (1968) updated with modern understanding of assembly factors, quality control checkpoints, and co-transcriptional assembly. All molecular components, assembly intermediates, and maturation factors have been validated against primary research sources. The logic gates represent actual regulatory checkpoints in ribosome biogenesis.",
